fields.label: Options for NextJS redirects
fields.message: If you want to change entire paths use :/slug Example we moved /blog/ to /news/ The Old URL will be /blog/:slug and the New url will be /news/:slug This will match anything after /blog/hello-world and push to /news/hello-world To change a wild card path use :slug* This will change the entire path: /blog/a/b/c/d/hello-world > /news/a/b/c/d/hello-world More information: https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next.config.js/redirects

fields.label: Rotator
fields.name: rotator
fields.instructions:
This field takes images that get applied to the rotator html within single-works.php.

You may drag the image items to change the order.

The images need a width to height ratio of 1.66, and in large windows could be displayed at 1500px wide or even wider. Really big images take longer to load, so there is a trade-off decision to be made when choosing images size. Smaller image will load fast, but might be a bit fuzzy in large windows.

fields.label: Hero_Image
fields.name: hero_image
fields.instructions:
This image appears as the first static image in the right column and at the top in mobiles. Replaces the rotator when the rotator is not used.

If a hero image is not selected, mobiles will not display a top image.
